Liechtenstein has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
For information on how to return to the UK from Liechtenstein, see Return to the UK
Entry and borders
The border with Switzerland remains open. However, the border crossings at Schellenberg and Mauren are closed. The border crossings at Ruggell and Schaanwald remain open for commuters, goods traffic and transit. Further restrictions and inspections may be in operation.
You may also wish to check our Travel Advice for Switzerland and Austria.
Local measures
Gatherings of more than 5 people are banned. This applies to all public and private events, including religious services. All restaurants, bars, leisure and entertainment facilities are closed. All educational establishments are also closed. Those aged over 65 or with pre-existing medical conditions are encouraged to stay at home.
All shops and markets have reopened and medical practitioners (including dentists) have resumed all non-urgent treatment. You can find more information on the emergency measures in place on the Government website (in German).
If you believe you have symptoms, you should not go directly to the hospital or a healthcare facility. Instead you should call the coronavirus emergency number on +423 235 45 32 (24 hours).
Further information
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
